==English==
[[Image:Mizoram in India (disputed hatched).svg|thumb|]]

===Etymology===
derived from mi (people), zo (lofty place, such as a hill) and ram (land), "land of the hill people"

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈmɪzəʊram/|/mɪˈzɔːrəm//mɪˈzɔərəm/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˌmɪzəˈræm/|lang=en}}

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# State in north-eastern [[India]] which has [[Aizawl]] as its [[capital]].

